        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 1:01AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 101 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Tuff, or near Leakey, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hunt, Mountain Home, Tuff, Leakey, Lost Maples State Natural Area,
Kerr Wildlife Management Area, and Vanderpool.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
